    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.51"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">51</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Ainsworth City Schools 
                        <lb/>
                    Ainsworth, Nebraska, 69210
                        <lb/>
                
                    Harold Deselms
                        <lb/>
                    Jr.-Sr. <hi rend="caps">H. S.</hi> Principal 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>October 3, 1972</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebr. 68508</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Ainsworth High School is now offering a nine-week course in Nebraska Writers. Naturally, your works are among those included in the course.</p>
                
                <p>We feel that all of our students would be very interested in knowing more about you and your work. If possible, we would like to work out some arrangement to have you here for a convocation and give our students a chance to visit with you.</p> 
                
                <p>Would you please let me know if you might be available to come. If you feel you could make the trip, we will work out financial arrangements with you.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute> 
                    
                    <signed>Harold Deselms</signed>
                    <signed>Harold Deselms</signed>
                
                    <note>ej</note> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
